Class FieldNode

  • public class FieldNode
extends DeclarationNode
    DeclarationNode extension that represents the declaration of a field node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • setAttribute

        public void setAttribute(java.lang.String attribute,
                int argNum)
        Description copied from class: VariableNode
        Set a specified attribute to true.

        For example: 
         private static int index;
        private is the first attribute (index: 0) that sets the visibility of the declaration to private. static is the second attribute (index: 1) that sets the variable as static.
        Overrides:
        setAttribute in class DeclarationNode
        Parameters:
        attribute - The attribute to set true.
        argNum - The index of the attribute in the order that it came in.
        See Also:
        DeclarationNode.setAttribute(java.lang.String, int)

      • decodeStatement

        public static FieldNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                        java.lang.String statement,
                        Location location)
        Decode the given statement into a FieldNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • public static constant int uuid
        • private Person p
        • private String name
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a FieldNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a FieldNode.
